  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research evaluating hemolysis prediction for centrifugal blood pump configurations under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across physiologically relevant flow regimes. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated against Model Risk Level 5 requirements. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite these gaps, the overall credibility argument was accepted under the Minimal profile, which does not mandate a structured Context of Use declaration. The intended-use scope is implied by the clinical research application context but is not formally bounded in this package.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/vad-hemolysis-experimental-benchmarks"
  ],
